I ordered from doordash but I called the store and spoke to Moe who claimed is the manager. I was able to order from door dash but when I called Moe stated they are not taking orders and their food delivery options are offline. He also said he didn’t receive my order even though door dash charged me and received my order. He lied and didn’t want to make the order because of the high volume of calls and orders he must have gotten. I was very disappointed. If they are not taking orders the food delivery pages shouldn’t have their restaurant listed on it. He didn’t want to cancel the order and have the customer waiting thinking they are going to receive the order. Good thing I called to confirm otherwise I would have been waiting. I called doordash and the rep said that the order went through successfully. I will never order from this place ever again. Horrible service.

I have been going to this place for a year and the wings are just fire. My favorite are the sweet thai chilli and the twisted toxic sauces and i don't think you can go wrong with those. They got the same sauce bosses behind the glass and register preparing the wings since they opened and they are both passionate and friendly people. The wings are thicc. Especially if you get them breaded style. Even their blue cheese is smooth and creamy and covers the wings in a blanket of flavors that create a pentagon of flavorful goodness. This is THE wing spot.

The place deserves only 2 stars because the wings were overcooked and very dry ,they were so hard I almost choked on one because it was impossible to break down .Even on the way home the wings smelled like old oil instead of delicious fresh fried chicken that can be smelled a mile away when cooked properly a fresh .They were super busy and overwhelmed that night so I will give them benefit of the doubt but I will not be returning to this place for sure .

These guys have a food truck that parks in LIC every day. Every day they block half of the busy crosswalk at Center and 47th, which is dangerous to begin with. Today, while moving the car that reserves the spot for the truck overnight and parking the truck they almost hit my daughter as she was crossing the street, then 15 minutes later almost backed over a woman trying to cross the street while using the crosswalk they were blocking. I don’t care how good or bad their food is, but these guys are making the neighborhood less safe, so we won’t be frequenting them

Okay so I've been here before and their fries were amazing and looked like the ones seen in all the other reviews, but today I got these fries which are a MASSIVE downgrade, they're thin and UNSALTED and incredibly hard, they tasted like they were straight out of the freezer. The wings are still great! Glad the quality of those didn't drop, but if there's a drop in quality in the fries due to the whole covid situation I wish that was told up front because I would just have not paid for the fries, they were awful. I guess if you're planning on ordering here just know that the fries have been changed and to not expect what's in the other reviews. $35 for two 7pc and three fries, when the fries look like frozen bag ones, really wasn't worth it. Should just stick to wings for now until it gets sorted out.

I seen this place a few weeks ago and today I decided to go in with some friends I had the honey garlic with the burger fries n mozzarella stick n the burger was sooo delicious the wind were so crispy n tasty love everything one of my friend had the mango habanero a lil spicy but so tasty n delicious I think the owner was there better nice guy he serve us he was been real nice I definently recommend my friends to try this place is amazing

Fantastic wings. Awesome customer service and very clean place!  It’s been such a long time since I’ve had great wings and of course being someone that strictly eats halal I’m limited to places where I’d be able to get wings but this by far beat all expectations. I’ve had wings from many different places, not just in Brooklyn but in other states as well. This hit the top of my list. Great sized wings and the boneless wings were actual chicken. Actual FRESH chicken. Nothing was frozen! It sounds like a joke when you say that the boneless wings were “actual chicken” but unfortunately I’ve had boneless wings that were actually nuggets from 95% of the places I’ve gone to. You have to try this for yourself to understand how great this is. Their customer base is very diverse and if you’re in nyc this is definitely worth making a trip to Brooklyn for.  They have a ton of options for their sauces as well - this was another unique factor. You guys have earned me as a repeat customer not only for the outstanding quality of the food but also the superb hospitality and customer service. I alongside my friend both felt welcomed from the moment I walked in. We were greeted with respect and I was given two pieces of the boneless wings to try them. This was of course after I told the person behind the register why I don’t go for boneless wings.  Thank you for a great experience, we absolutely loved it! I wish I had taken more pictures before digging in to the food.

So I normally don't review anything, but couldn't let this be unsaid. Those wings were great. Soup was on point. But what really stood out was how friendly they were in there. Thanks for the amazing lunch and great service! Whoever was working the register was the friendliest person I've ever interacted with, you guys have a customer for life!
First time ordering from here and let me tell you the staff was absolutely pleasant to deal with and the food was amazing. Definitely my new go to place.

The perfect place to have some delicious wings.
Sweet thai chili is my new fav seasoning because of this place. Couldn’t recommend this place more. The burgers are also surprisingly flavorful. Definitely coming back.

Want a little extra on the side, order you some twisted mozzarella sticks. Feeling a lil healthy, get some zucchini sticks instead. You’ll walk out saying BWW who? Atomic Wings what? Never heard of em after Twisted Wings. Cheers to the flyest wing spot in Brooklyn, I’LL BE BACK!

The food was great here, the wings were great and the flavours were delicious. Mohammed was a great server. Excellent customer service. One thing that stood out was the fact that he allowed us to try the different sauces before ordering. Would deffo recommend and would deffo come here again.

The food was amazing and the customer service was second to none. Mohamed made sure our experience was one to remember and he allowed us to taste the sauces making sure we ordered the flavour we wanted. I would defo take a flight from the UK to come again.

This spot is definitely a go to!!! The wings are so delicious and FRESH! Best of all it is halal. My favorite sauce is sweet Thai chili! The staff are very welcoming and friendly. If you haven’t stopped here please make it someday. I promise you won’t be disappointed!

I went to twisted wings for the first time a few days ago and I wasn't sure what I was getting myself into but I was pleasantly surprised. The man behind the register was very amiable and helpful in deciding which wing sauce I should get (side note: This place has breaded wings?!?!), I ended up trying the Sweet Thai Chile sauce with the breaded wings which was also a pleasant surprise. All in all I had a wonderful experience and will be coming back to satisfy my wings fix!
Best wings I've had in a while, definitely worth going back for.

I don't normally write reviews but I'm writing this because I experienced this amazing place.  I walked into Twisted wings and was immediately greeted by the man behind the counter. There we're a lot of options so he guided us through what we needed. The food was great but most importantly while there was no one in the store being tended too he asked me how me day was. It's amazing how many people go inside your store and they just see you as a customer but for him it felt like he deeply cared. Not only for me but many of the customers are experienced the same thing  When I left he didn't ask for anything just waved have a good day and at that time it deeply touched my heart.  I recommend it to everyone, the food is amazing but the customer service is impeccable.

the moment I walked in,  I was greeted very kindly by the front desk. They let me taste test their sauces, till I found the right one for me. I got them on the boneless and the naked wings and wow. Fresh great quality wings cooked to perfection and the sauce was just mouth watering. After I finished my food I bought some more to go. Better than buffalo Wild Wings and the customer service is top notch.

They just opened up in this area. My experience is only with wings but they have more to offer from the menu. I have ordered and stopped by to pick up and both experiences were great.  The staff is very friendly and nice. They are patient and knowledgeable with what they have. I have seen them answer questions for customers who have never had wings or sauces like this and offer a tasting of the sauces.  The wings were super delicious, definitely not cheap freezer bag wings from a store. The sauces are amazing. I have so far only tried the Sriracha honey (spicy with a hint of sweetness), Garlic Parmesan, Honey Mustard and Sweet and Sour. All the sauces are delicious. They have a lot of sauce choices which is a good thing and there is a flavor for everyone to enjoy.  I would highly recommend the twisted combo because it comes with blue cheese, carrots/ celery, fries (that taste great, even without ketchup), wings and can of soda.  Glad to have something like this place in this neighborhood and recommend everyone check them out!

Horrible wings place, do not order from here! Ordered through GrubHub, I get a call that they don’t have honey bbq sauce. What kind of wing place runs out of honey bbq sauce? Then I say to give me a sweet bbq sauce and they send me an incredibly spicy chipotle sauce I couldn’t even eat it. The fries were soggy and came in a cardboard box with water in it. Took well over an hour to come. Horrible food, horrible customer service, never again.
Best wings ever I try the Buffalo gold best thing ever definitely going back🤤😍

My wife and I went to the soft opening of Twisted Wings on 11/19/2019. Even though they haven't officially opened yet, we were greeted warmly if not enthusiastically and everything was in order and ready to go. My wife, who has a food handlers certificate, noticed that each sauce had it's own separate pair of tongs, so someone there knows about safe food preparation. I ordered the naked Sweet Thai Chile and my wife had the naked Honey Honey. The wings were big, meaty and fried perfectly. The Sweet Thai Chile was pleasantly but not insanely hot with just the right amount of sweetness and the sauce made a nice glaze. The Honey Honey was sweet with a nice mustard tang.  It took more than twenty minutes to get the order out but I'm going to chalk that up to inexperience. I have no doubt that they'll find their groove and speed up. We're definitely coming back.
We had honey BBQ wings and burger. They were all yummy! And the fries were perfect. Would visit again to try other flavors of the wings!!
Definitely my new spot for wings!!! Its gonna take me some time to try all the different flavors.
